events.description: Avar–Byzantine wars: The Avars lift the siege at the Byzantine stronghold of Tomis. Their leader Bayan I retreats north of the Danube River after the Avaro-Slavic army is decimated by the plague.
events.html: • 598 – Avar–Byzantine wars: The Avars lift the siege at the Byzantine stronghold of Tomis. Their leader Bayan I retreats north of the Danube River after the Avaro-Slavic army is decimated by the plague.

events.description: The people of Sicily rebel against the Angevin king Charles I, in what becomes known as the Sicilian Vespers.
events.html: • 1282 – The people of Sicily rebel against the Angevin king Charles I, in what becomes known as the Sicilian Vespers.[1]

events.description: Edward I sacks Berwick-upon-Tweed, during armed conflict between Scotland and England.
events.html: • 1296 – Edward I sacks Berwick-upon-Tweed, during armed conflict between Scotland and England.[2]

events.description: Guru Gobind Singh establishes the Khalsa in Anandpur Sahib, Punjab.
events.html: • 1699 – Guru Gobind Singh establishes the Khalsa in Anandpur Sahib, Punjab.[3]

events.description: Joachim Murat issues the Rimini Proclamation, among the earliest calls for Italian unification.
events.html: • 1815 – Joachim Murat issues the Rimini Proclamation, among the earliest calls for Italian unification.[4][5]

events.description: Physicist Augustin Fresnel reads a memoir on optical rotation to the French Academy of Sciences, reporting that when polarized light is "depolarized" by a Fresnel rhomb, its properties are preserved in any subsequent passage through an optically-rotating crystal or liquid.
events.html: • 1818 – Physicist Augustin Fresnel reads a memoir on optical rotation to the French Academy of Sciences, reporting that when polarized light is "depolarized" by a Fresnel rhomb, its properties are preserved in any subsequent passage through an optically-rotating crystal or liquid.[6]

events.description: The Florida Territory is created in the United States.
events.html: • 1822 – The Florida Territory is created in the United States.

events.description: The National Bank of Greece is founded in Athens.
events.html: • 1841 – The National Bank of Greece is founded in Athens.

events.description: Ether anesthesia is used for the first time, in an operation by the American surgeon Dr. Crawford Long.
events.html: • 1842 – Ether anesthesia is used for the first time, in an operation by the American surgeon Dr. Crawford Long.

events.description: One of the most important battles of the Dominican War of Independence from Haiti takes place near the city of Santiago de los Caballeros.
events.html: • 1844 – One of the most important battles of the Dominican War of Independence from Haiti takes place near the city of Santiago de los Caballeros.

events.description: Origins of the American Civil War: "Border Ruffians" from Missouri invade Kansas and force election of a pro-slavery legislature.
events.html: • 1855 – Origins of the American Civil War: "Border Ruffians" from Missouri invade Kansas and force election of a pro-slavery legislature.

entities.name: Origins of the American Civil War

events.description: The Treaty of Paris is signed, ending the Crimean War.
events.html: • 1856 – The Treaty of Paris is signed, ending the Crimean War.

events.description: Discovery of the chemical elements: Sir William Crookes announces his discovery of thallium.
events.html: • 1861 – Discovery of the chemical elements: Sir William Crookes announces his discovery of thallium.

events.description: Danish prince Wilhelm Georg is chosen as King George of Greece.
events.html: • 1863 – Danish prince Wilhelm Georg is chosen as King George of Greece.

events.description: Alaska is purchased from Russia for $7.2 million, about two cents/acre ($4.19/km2), by United States Secretary of State William H. Seward.
events.html: • 1867 – Alaska is purchased from Russia for $7.2 million, about two cents/acre ($4.19/km2), by United States Secretary of State William H. Seward.

events.description: Texas is readmitted to the United States Congress following Reconstruction.
events.html: • 1870 – Texas is readmitted to the United States Congress following Reconstruction.

events.description: The Battle for Kushka triggers the Panjdeh Incident which nearly gives rise to war between the Russian and British Empires.
events.html: • 1885 – The Battle for Kushka triggers the Panjdeh Incident which nearly gives rise to war between the Russian and British Empires.

events.description: German Society of Chemistry issues an invitation to other national scientific organizations to appoint delegates to the International Committee on Atomic Weights.

events.description: Archaeologists in Knossos, Crete, discover the first clay tablet with hieroglyphic writing in a script later called Linear B.
events.html: • 1900 – Archaeologists in Knossos, Crete, discover the first clay tablet with hieroglyphic writing in a script later called Linear B.[7]

events.description: Sultan Abd al-Hafid signs the Treaty of Fez, making Morocco a French protectorate.
events.html: • 1912 – Sultan Abd al-Hafid signs the Treaty of Fez, making Morocco a French protectorate.

events.description: Beginning of the bloody March Events in Baku and other locations of Baku Governorate.
events.html: • 1918 – Beginning of the bloody March Events in Baku and other locations of Baku Governorate.

events.description: The Heinkel He 100 fighter sets a world airspeed record of 463 mph (745 km/h).
events.html: • 1939 – The Heinkel He 100 fighter sets a world airspeed record of 463 mph (745 km/h).

events.description: Second Sino-Japanese War: Japan declares Nanking capital of a new Chinese puppet government, nominally controlled by Wang Jingwei.

events.description: World War II: Allied bombers conduct their most severe bombing run on Sofia, Bulgaria.

events.description: Out of 795 Lancasters, Halifaxes and Mosquitos sent to attack Nuremberg, 95 bombers do not return, making it the largest RAF Bomber Command loss of the war.

events.description: World War II: Soviet forces invade Austria and capture Vienna. Polish and Soviet forces liberate Danzig.

events.description: Cold War: A riot breaks out in Austurvöllur square in Reykjavík, when Iceland joins NATO.

events.description: Tenzin Gyatso, the 14th Dalai Lama, flees Tibet for India.

events.description: The Single Convention on Narcotic Drugs is signed in New York City.
events.html: • 1961 – The Single Convention on Narcotic Drugs is signed in New York City.

events.html: • 1965 – Vietnam War: A car bomb explodes in front of the United States Embassy, Saigon, killing 22 and wounding 183 others.

events.description: Delta Air Lines Flight 9877 crashes at Louis Armstrong New Orleans International Airport, killing 19.

events.description: Vietnam War: The Easter Offensive begins after North Vietnamese forces cross into the Demilitarized Zone (DMZ) of South Vietnam.

events.description: Israeli-Palestinian conflict: in the first organized response against Israeli policies by a Palestinian collective since 1948, Palestinians create the first Land Day.

events.description: Airey Neave, a British Member of Parliament (MP), is killed by a car bomb as he exits the Palace of Westminster. The Irish National Liberation Army claims responsibility.
